HB 593 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Henry
Abstract: Increases the maximum local service and transaction fee limits to generate
funding for office of motor vehicles field offices, not fully funded by the state.
Present law allows local governments to implement a fee for each service or transaction
carried out at an office of motor vehicles field office that is not fully funded by the state.
Present law limits this fee to $4.50 per transaction, except for Orleans, Jefferson and
Calcasieu parishes which may charge up to $6, and the city of West Monroe which may
charge up to $8. Present law mandates that revenue generated from these fees be used for
facility rental, utilities, and maintenance. Present law prohibits charging a fee for the
acquisition or renewal of a motor vehicle registration license.
Proposed law increases the maximum local service and transaction fee amount in present law
from $4.50 to $8 statewide. Also removes the authority granted to Orleans, Jefferson,
Calcasieu, and West Monroe parishes regarding maximum service and transaction fees.
Proposed law provides an exemption for office of motor vehicle field offices in Shreveport,
Louisiana.
(Amends R.S. 32:429(A))
